title: Bug 109350 - Output parameter not displayed in data set dialog
description: The output parameter is not being displayed in the data set dialog when it should be.
OB: While on the query result page, there is no data returned. The actual result is that the output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
EB: I expect that when on the query result page, the output parameter should be visible and editable in the data set dialog.
SR:
To reproduce this issue, follow these steps:
1. Call the stored procedure from the Oracle database.
2. Check the query result, which should be stored in the output parameter as an object.
